# üìò Comfy-WaveSpeed Dynamic Caching Optimisation

## üîç Overview

In [Issue #87](https://github.com/chengzeyi/Comfy-WaveSpeed/issues/87), user `easygoing0114` conducted tests on the Dynamic Caching feature using the `Flux.1-dev Anime Model`. The goal was to determine optimal settings for improved generation quality and performance.

## ‚öôÔ∏è Tested Configurations

Two configurations were compared:

### Configuration 1: Baseline

* `start = 0`
* `end = 1`
* `max_consecutive_cache_hits = -1`

### Configuration 2: Optimised

* `start = 0.2`
* `end = 0.8`
* `max_consecutive_cache_hits = 5`

The small numbers in the graphs represent the `residual_diff_threshold`.([GitHub][1])

## üìä Results

The optimised settings (`start = 0.2`, `end = 0.8`, `max_consecutive_cache_hits = 5`) demonstrated superior results in terms of generation quality and performance.

## ‚úÖ Recommendation

For users aiming to enhance generation quality and performance in Comfy-WaveSpeed, it is recommended to apply the following Dynamic Caching settings:

* `start = 0.2`
* `end = 0.8`
* `max_consecutive_cache_hits = 5`

These settings have been shown to provide better results compared to the baseline configuration.

---

For more detailed information and discussions, refer to the original issue: [Comfy-WaveSpeed Issue #87](https://github.com/chengzeyi/Comfy-WaveSpeed/issues/87).

---

# üß† ComfyUI-OllamaGemini Custom Node Setup Guide

Set up the [ComfyUI-OllamaGemini](https://github.com/al-swaiti/ComfyUI-OllamaGemini/tree/dev) custom node to integrate with Gemini, OpenAI, Claude, and other LLMs.

---

## üóÇ Step 1: Clone the Repository

### üîß On Linux/macOS:

Open a terminal and run:

```bash
cd /path/to/ComfyUI/custom_nodes
git clone https://github.com/al-swaiti/ComfyUI-OllamaGemini.git
```

### ü™ü On Windows:

Open **Command Prompt** or **PowerShell**, then run:

```powershell
cd path\to\ComfyUI\custom_nodes
git clone https://github.com/al-swaiti/ComfyUI-OllamaGemini.git
```

---

## üîê Step 2: Get Your Gemini API Key

1. Visit [https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey](https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey)
2. Sign in with your Google account.
3. Copy the **Gemini API Key**.

---

## üõ† Step 3: Configure Your API Keys

Open (or create) the following file:

```
ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ComfyUI-OllamaGemini/config.json
```

Paste and edit the configuration like this:

```json
{
  "GEMINI_API_KEY": "your_gemini_api_key",
  "OPENAI_API_KEY": "your_openai_api_key",
  "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY": "your_claude_api_key",
  "OLLAMA_URL": "http://localhost:11434",
  "QWEN_API_KEY": "your_qwen_api_key"
}
```

‚ùó You may leave unused API keys as empty strings (`""`) or delete those lines.

---

## ‚úÖ Final Step

Restart ComfyUI. The new custom node should now be available and ready for use with Gemini and other models.

---

# üîÆ Transform Your Images with Natural Language Instructions

## The Perfect Companion for Seamless Editing

This guide outlines a complete workflow using **FluxFill-Dev** with **ICEdit-MoE-LoRA** for powerful natural language-based image editing.

## üìù Overview: The Future of Image Editing is Here

ICEdit-MoE-LoRA represents a breakthrough in AI image editing - a lightweight Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA) module that brings professional-grade, instruction-based editing capabilities to large diffusion transformers. By intelligently fine-tuning only 1% of parameters using just 0.5% of the original training data, it achieves extraordinary editing capabilities that match or even surpass premium commercial solutions.

## üìå Complete Workflow

This workflow combines FluxFill + ICEdit-MoE-LoRA for editing images with natural language instructions. For enhanced results,   diffusion models like [LEOPARD](https://civitai.com/models/1534861) , [Bernoulli](https://civitai.com/models/682369) or [SPEED_Q8](https://civitai.com/models/661102/speedq8) with the Gemini auto prompt node in 4-8 steps.(i used very light flux model which need less steps)

## üõ†Ô∏è Complete Installation Guide

### üìÅ Perfect Setup Structure

```
üìÇ ComfyUI/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ üìÇ models/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ üìÇ diffusion_models/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ (basic)üìÑ fluxfill-dev.safetensors # https://civitai.com/models/1108146/fluxfill-devgguf
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ(option1)üìÑ LEOPARD.gguf     # https://civitai.com/models/1534861
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ(option2)üìÑ Bernoulli.gguf  # https://civitai.com/models/682369
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ(option3)üìÑ SPEED_Q8.gguf   # https://civitai.com/models/661102/speedq8
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ üìÇ text_encoders/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ (basic)üìÑ clip_l.safetensors
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ (option1)üìÑ t5xxl_fp16.safetensors
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ (option2)üìÑ t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ (option3)üìÑ t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled.safetensors
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ üìÇ vae/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ üìÑ ae.safetensors
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ üìÇ lora/
‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ üìÑ ICEdit-MoE.safetensors
```

## üíé Essential Components

### üî§ Text Encoders - The Brain Behind Natural Language Understanding
**Note: You only need to choose ONE of the T5XXL options below based on your hardware capabilities**

- [**clip_l.safetensors** - Core understanding model](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/stable-diffusion-3.5-fp8/blob/main/text_encoders/clip_l.safetensors)
- **T5XXL Options** (choose only one):
  - [**t5xxl_fp16.safetensors** - Highest quality, more demanding](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/stable-diffusion-3.5-fp8/blob/main/text_encoders/t5xxl_fp16.safetensors)
  - [**t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors** - Balanced performance](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/stable-diffusion-3.5-fp8/blob/main/text_encoders/t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors)
  - [**t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled.safetensors** - Optimized for speed](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/stable-diffusion-3.5-fp8/blob/main/text_encoders/t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled.safetensors)

### üé≠ VAE - The Visual Artist

- [**ae.safetensors** - Included in the FluxFill package](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/HiDream-I1_ComfyUI/resolve/main/split_files/vae/ae.safetensors?download=true)

### üñºÔ∏è Diffusion Models - The Imaging Engine 

- [**fluxfill-dev.safetensors** - Core diffusion model for editing](https://civitai.com/models/1108146/fluxfill-devgguf)

##(You only need to choose ONE of those or use flux-dev itself its up to u)
- [**LEOPARD.safetensors** - Advanced diffusion model for refined outputs](https://civitai.com/models/1534861)
- [**Bernoulli.safetensors** - Alternative diffusion model for enhanced generation](https://civitai.com/models/682369)
- [**SPEED_Q8.gguf** - Enhanced flux-dev model for improved results](https://civitai.com/models/661102/speedq8)

**Note:** Any of these diffusion models can be used for efficient editing with fewer steps (4-8 steps recommended). Use flux-dev-fill for editing and flux-dev  for enhancing results.

### ‚ú® LoRA Models - The Magic Touch

- [**ICEdit-MoE.safetensors** - The star of the show!](https://civitai.com/models/315428/icedit-moe-lora-for-realistic-image-editing-with-text-instructions)
